		<div class="right"><a href="index.html"><img src="../sle.png" alt="SLE 2012 SI"></a><br><code>sle2012s/paper02</code></div>
			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2012 SI</a> paper:</span><br><i>Using a trope-based foundational ontology for bridging different areas of concern in ontology-driven conceptual modeling</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/GiancarloGuizzardi.html">Giancarlo Guizzardi</a>, <a href="../profile/VeruskaZamborlini.html">Veruska Zamborlini</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.scico.2014.02.022">10.1016/j.scico.2014.02.022</a></li>
<li>Extended version of <a href="../sle2012/paper16.html"><em>A Common Foundational Theory for Bridging Two Levels in Ontology-Driven Conceptual Modeling</em></a> (SLE 2012)</li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3e.html"><span class="tagM">T3E: Ontologies</span></a><ul><li> The contribution is a foundational ontology (objects, tropes) used to ground conceptual modelling and interoperability.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1d.html"><span class="tagL">T1D: Composition</span></a><ul><li> The paper explicitly aims to bridge distinct “areas of concern” and phases (conceptual modelling vs implementation concerns) through coordinated artefacts.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4b.html"><span class="tagL">T4B: Horizontal Transformation</span></a><ul><li> It provides mapping directives to connect OntoUML models with OWL/Semantic Web representations, i.e., horizontal mapping/conversion between formalisms.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> It discusses computational/tool support for model building, transformation, and manipulation based on the proposed ontological foundations.
</li></ul></li></ul>
		<clear/>
		<footer/>
